<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-161-676  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 161 676.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Feb 19 1990 v7 n7 p43(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PC DOCS 2.1 speeds document searches within WordPerfect. (CS/DataCorp. document management system) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Higgins, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   CMS Data Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   PC DOCS 2.1 (Medical/health software) (product introduction)WordPerfect (Word processing software) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Document Management SystemsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Steve HigginsandM;CMS/Data Corp. last week put more power at the fingertips of users of its PCDOCS document-management system with a new release that allows documentsearches in as few as two keystrokes.andM;PC DOCS version 2.1 speeds searches for WordPerfect documents on Novell Inc.andO;NetWare LANs as long as users have previously noted the document numbers,company officials said.andP;  Users can bypass the more time-consuming &quot;profile&quot;step and skip right to the search by hitting a function key followed by thedocument number.andM;&quot;Now it's a one-step procedure to pull up a document if you know its number,&quot;said Karen Fate, systems manager at Dallas law firm Gardere andamp; Wynne and abeta tester of PC DOCS 2.1.andP;  Users who don't know a document's number, sheadded, can still call up the profile screen and enter more generalinformation, such as key words, to search for the document.andM;The time savings provided in the new version, though measured &quot;probably inseconds&quot; for each search, can be a great convenience over the long term, saidPat Kite, a user-training coordinator at Womble, Carlyle, Sandridge and Rice,a Winston-Salem, N.C., law firm.andM;Another key feature, Fate said, is the close integration of the package withWordPerfect Corp.'s word processor.andP;  Because PC DOCS works from withinWordPerfect, it forces a user creating a WordPerfect document to enter itinto the PC DOCS system, she explained.andM;&quot;When users make a document, we want them to be forced to fill out theprofile screen,&quot; which ensures that the firm can keep track of all documents,she said.andM;PC DOCS also enables supervisors to maintain the integrity of certaindocuments, such as templates, by locking out all changes to them.andP;  Each timea document is created, it can be deemed a &quot;master document,&quot; which allows itto be copied but not altered, company officials said.andM;PC DOCS version 2.1 is now available from the firm for $195 per workstation.andM;CMS/Data Corp., of Tallahassee, Fla., can be reached at (800) 933-DOCS.andO;</TEXT></DOC>